The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) yesterday submitted the names of Musa Wada as its candidate for the November 16 governorship election in Kogi State to the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). The party also submitted to INEC, Samuel Bamidele Aro, a former member of the House of Representatives as the running mate to Engr. Wada. A top party source confirmed to our correspondent last night that Hon. Aro, who represented Yagba Federal Constituency in the House of Representatives, was favoured as running mate after extensive consultations and accord by critical stakeholders in the state. Daily Trust learnt that the PDP Governorship Election Appeal Committee set up to review the Kogi and Bayelsa states governorship election primaries also upheld the election of Engr. Musa Wada as the party’s candidate. A copy of the report seen by our correspondent showed that the panel led by the National Chairman of the party, Prince Uche Secondus, undertook a comprehensive review of the petition brought before it by Senator Dino Melaye and Alhaji Abubakar Ibrahim Idris who participated in the primaries. No petition was received from any of the aspirants that contested in the Bayelsa State primary where Senator Douye Diri emerged as the party’s governorship candidate. Wada, Aro make INEC list as PDP guber candidate, running mate for Kogi Bello vs Wada: Plus, minus of Kogi’s leading guber candidates Crisis rocks PDP over Wada's emergence as Kogi gov’ship candidate OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY